6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1021, L.D. 1563, “An Act to Establish
10 Content Standards for Legislation”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 39 in §1051 in the first indented paragraph in the first
12 line (page 1, line 6 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "All legislation drafted for
13 introduction to the Legislature" and inserting the following: 'Beginning with the 133rd
14 Legislature, all legislation drafted for introduction to the Legislature, with the exception of
15 uniform laws and the supplemental and biennial budgets,'
16 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
17 number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, amends the
2200 requirement in the bill that all legislation drafted for introduction to the Legislature must
2211 be written in a manner that allows it to become law if not amended and may not be an
2222 abstract or concept of the intent of the legislation by excluding uniform laws and the
2233 supplemental and biennial budgets from the requirement. The amendment also provides
2244 that the requirement begins with the 133rd Legislature.
